===Other Equipment===
{{Quote|This suit, it comes with expectations, brother.|[[Lemar Hoskins]] to John Walker|The Star-Spangled Man}}
*'''[[Captain America's Uniform|Captain America Uniform]]''': [[File:U.S. Agent (2024).jpg|thumb|250px|Walker dons his Captain America suit]] As Captain America, Walker wore a blue and red uniform similar to those worn by Steve Rogers. Like Rogers' helmet, his helmet featured a symbol representing the combination of the letter "A" and a star. The same symbol was located on the right side of his chest and on the back of his uniform, where the shield was stored. The uniform incorporates advanced armor, with the reinforced helmet being capable of containing the blast from a grenade explosion.
{{Quote|It's the [[Captain America's Uniform|same]]. But black.|U.S. Agent to [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]]|One World, One People}}
*'''[[U.S. Agent's Uniform|U.S. Agent Uniform]]''': Walker was given a replacement for his Captain America uniform once he was recruited by [[Valentina Allegra de Fontaine]] to serve as the U.S. Agent. The uniform has a highly similar design to his Captain America uniform, but is black rather than blue with red and white stripes in the same place as the red stripes on the Captain America uniform, with only one, barely visible, "A" and star symbol on the chest.
{{Quote|Walker, shield!|[[Ghost]] to U.S. Agent|Thunderbolts*}}
*'''[[U.S. Agent's Shield|Shield]]''': [[File:Thunderbolts D23 Brazil Special Look (21).png|thumb|250px|Walker defends himself with his shield]] Upon becoming U.S. Agent, Walker wielded a newer shield with dark orange-bronze line on it, while the rest is plain shaded gray. The shield was made with a highly durable material, allowing it to withstand forceful impact and rapid gunfire from assault weapons. However, [[Sentry]] was able to bend the shield during the [[Battle at the Watchtower]].

===Vehicles===
*'''{{WPS|MD Helicopters MH-6 Little Bird|MH-6 Helicopter}}''': Walker and [[Lemar Hoskins]] flew in a helicopter to help [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] and [[Winter Soldier]] fight the [[Flag Smashers]] in [[Munich]], [[Germany]]. Walker stood on one of the landing skids as he threw his [[Captain America's Shield|shield]] to stun [[Karli Morgenthau]] before leaping off the helicopter to join the fight.
*'''{{WPS|Tarpan Honker|1990 Tarpan Honker}}''': In order to return to the airport following their defeat at the hands of the Flag Smashers, Walker and Hoskins rode a military Jeep, and offered Wilson and Barnes a lift with them, which they rejected.
*'''[[Red Guardian's Limousine]]''': After [[Escape from the O.X.E. Vault|escaping]] the [[O.X.E. Vault]], Walker and his allies were picked up by [[Red Guardian]] in his limo. 

===Former Equipment===
{{Quote|Just 'cause you carry that [[Captain America's Shield|shield]], it doesn't mean you're Captain America.|[[Bucky Barnes]] to John Walker|The Star-Spangled Man}}
*'''[[Captain America's Shield]]''': [[File:Captain America (John Walker).jpg|thumb|250px|Captain America holding the shield]] When Walker was chosen to be the second Captain America, he was entrusted with the shield to aid in his missions. Since then, Walker has used it in a manner similar to [[Steve Rogers|his predecessor]] by utilizing it in a primarily defensive manner and throwing it in an offensive manner. However, due to his aggressive personality, Walker has used the shield with lethal intent, such as when he killed [[Nico]]. Nico's murder resulted in [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] reclaiming the shield with the aid of [[Winter Soldier]] in order to put an end to his rampage.
*'''[[John Walker's Shield|Homemade Shield]]''': After losing Captain America's shield to [[Sam Wilson|Falcon]] and [[Winter Soldier]], getting stripped of the Captain America title, and being other than honorably discharged from the United States Army, Walker forged his own version of the shield with a similar but distinct design, decorating it with the medals he had worn throughout his military career. However, while it protected Walker adequately, the new shield was nowhere near as durable as the [[vibranium]] shield and of little use as an actual weapon due to the common metal used, and ended up battered and dented by the time Walker abandoned his rampage.

==Facilities==
*'''[[Custer's Grove High School]]''': [[File:Locker Room.png|thumb|250px|Walker looks at his old locker and new suit]] Walker attended Custer's Grove High School, where he was the captain of the football team and according to [[Lemar Hoskins]], failed drama class. Walker later returned to his high school for an interview about him succeeding [[Steve Rogers]] as Captain America.
*'''[[John Walker's House|House]]''': Walker lived with his wife and son in their home until he and Olivia got divorced. 
*'''[[Watchtower]]''': As a member of the [[New Avengers]], Walker operated from and resided in the Watchtower.

